headline: Is Target Stock Going Private? 1 Analyst Thinks the Answer Could Be ‘Yes.’
summary: Analysts at D.A. Davidson named Target a potential leveraged buyout candidate, suggesting a $108 per-share takeout requiring roughly $37 billion in debt and $12 billion in equity, which would make it one of the largest private equity deals ever.
